===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|chaine|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|chaine|lang=fro}}, {{term|chaene|lang=fro}} {{gloss|"chain"; Modern French: {{term|chaîne|lang=fr}}}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|catena|catēna|chain|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro}} {{recons|kat-||to braid, twist; hut, shed|lang=ine-pro}}. Cognate with {{etyl|frr|-}} {{term|ketten||chain|lang=frr}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|keten||chain|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|nds|-}} {{term|Kede||chain|lang=nds}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Kette||chain|lang=de}}, {{etyl|da|-}} {{term|kæde||chain|lang=da}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|kedja||chain|lang=sv}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|keðja||chain|lang=is}}.

